teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Test heavy', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Worst prof I have had in my undergraduate career. You can tell she is a professor for the research, and not for the teaching. She just has us read multiple 15 page papers before each class and summarizes it. You are graded solely on your ability to memorize said papers. You can study for weeks and still fail. Do better.

Classes these days are boring because you know exactly what to expect. I want to be surprised. I want my teachers to answer in a cryptic and vague manner. I want the course notes to be almost empty. This way, I have to figure things out on my own. This course is like a thriller book, it will keep you on the edge of a loaded revolver.

Very passionate about science and more specifically proteins. Puts a lot of effort into her class material and is open to discussion following courses. Does ramble off on tangents occasionally and might lose track of time during teaching. Overall great prof and great course as long as you put in the effort necessary.
Worst prof ever. Memorize everything down to the little details and regurgitate. If you want to learn something, don't take it with Carrier. She is nice, true, but she is not a good teacher.

I don't regret taking this course with her, she is really nice and caring, always there to answer questions, and she's very knowledgeable. Her exams are not easy, requires a lot of memorization, but they had no surprises. She's however giving hints in class which is really nice. I suggest doing your very best on the labs if you want an A

very kind professor who cares about her students. i dont understand why she has such a bad rating. I got a 9 in the course so it is possible to do well. you can't expect to do well, if you put no effort.
good professor. she explains very clearly the material and cares about her students. the exams are tough but if you study, you will do well.
